com.esri.mo2.map.ext
Interface GeoCodeStyle

All Superinterfaces:
Cloneable
All Known Implementing Classes:
BaseGeoCodeStyle
public interface GeoCodeStyle
extends Cloneable

Defines an address-matching style. The style is typically defined within a properties file, and consists of "definition tags" for Fields that define the geocoding operation and "input tags" that specify the Fields required for performing the geocode search operation. All tag values are String data types.

getInputTagType

public String getInputTagType(int index)
Returns the type of an input tag for the specified tag index. The result will be a string that consists of either the value "TEXT" to indicate that the end-user must type in a text value, or the value "COMBO" followed by a comma-separated list of values. For example "COMBO Sydney,Papeete,Los Angeles".

Parameters:
index - the tag index
Returns:
the input tag type
